---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { BookOpen, AlertCircle, Printer, X, Check, Lock, ChevronRight, Terminal } from 'lucide-react';
---

<Layout title="System Documentation - Nomade Cuisine">
    <div class="min-h-screen bg-stone-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            {/* Header */}
            <div class="mb-10 text-center">
                <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6 shadow-sm">
                    <BookOpen size={32} className="text-emerald-600" />
                </div>
                <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 tracking-tight mb-4">Site Documentation</h1>
                <p class="text-stone-500 font-medium text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                    Official reference guide for Nomade Cuisine's digital POS systems, hardware configurations, and automated dashboards.
                </p>
            </div>

            {/* Content Blocks */}
            <div class="space-y-8">
                
                {/* Dashboard Lock */}
                <section class="bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-8 sm:p-10 border border-stone-200 shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)] relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-5">
                        <Lock size={120} />
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 relative z-10">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-amber-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-amber-100">
                            <Lock size={20} className="text-amber-600" />
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">1. Counter Dashboard Security</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prose prose-stone prose-emerald max-w-none relative z-10">
                        <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed">
                            The Counter Dashboard (<code>/counter</code>) is protected by a client-side PIN pad. This ensures that unauthorized individuals cannot interact with, accept, or reject incoming web orders while the tablet is left unattended.
                        </p>
                        <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-4 mt-4 inline-block font-mono text-sm font-bold text-stone-700">
                            Default Security PIN: <span class="bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">8888</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                {/* Online Store Live Toggle */}
                <section class="bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-8 sm:p-10 border border-stone-200 shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)] relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-5">
                        <Check size={120} />
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 relative z-10">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-blue-100">
                            <AlertCircle size={20} className="text-blue-600" />
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">2. Store Status Toggles</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prose prose-stone prose-emerald max-w-none relative z-10 space-y-6">
                        <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed">
                            Through the Settings ⚙️ icon on the top right of the Counter Dashboard, a Manager can independently toggle whether the store is accepting digital orders or not.
                        </p>
                        
                        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                            <div class="bg-emerald-50/50 border border-emerald-100 rounded-2xl p-5">
                                <h3 class="flex items-center gap-2 font-black text-emerald-800 text-lg mb-2">
                                    <Check size={18} strokeWidth={3} /> Online Orders Live
                                </h3>
                                <p class="text-sm text-emerald-700/80 font-medium leading-relaxed">
                                    Customers scanning the QR menus at their tables can actively browse the menu, add items to their cart, and submit them directly to the counter for fulfillment.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="bg-red-50/50 border border-red-100 rounded-2xl p-5">
                                <h3 class="flex items-center gap-2 font-black text-red-800 text-lg mb-2">
                                    <X size={18} strokeWidth={3} /> Ordering Is Paused
                                </h3>
                                <p class="text-sm text-red-700/80 font-medium leading-relaxed">
                                    Customers can still look at the menu, but placing orders is blocked. An "Ordering is currently paused" popup is displayed to them. Excellent for rush hours.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                {/* Customer Security PIN */}
                <section class="bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-8 sm:p-10 border border-stone-200 shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)] relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-5">
                        <Lock size={120} />
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 relative z-10">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-indigo-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-indigo-100">
                            <Lock size={20} className="text-indigo-600" />
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">3. Customer Security PIN</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prose prose-stone prose-emerald max-w-none relative z-10 space-y-6">
                        <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed">
                            To ensure only customers physically present in the restaurant can place orders, Nomade Cuisine utilizes a <strong>Daily Security PIN</strong>. This prevents "Remote Spam" where people at home scan photos of your menu and send fake orders to your kitchen.
                        </p>
                        
                        <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden divide-y divide-stone-200">
                            <div class="p-6">
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">How The System Works</h3>
                                <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed text-sm">
                                    When a customer clicks <strong>"Send to Counter"</strong>, the website will prompt them to enter a 4-digit code. If they do not enter the correct code, the order is instantly rejected by the server. 
                                    By writing this code on a physical chalkboard or on your printed menus, you create an "analog geofence" that only physical guests can cross.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="p-6 bg-white border-l-4 border-indigo-500">
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-indigo-900 mb-2">Changing the PIN</h3>
                                <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
                                    You can change the PIN at any time via the <strong>Settings ⚙️ Drawer</strong> on the Counter Dashboard:
                                </p>
                                <ul class="text-sm font-medium text-stone-600 list-disc pl-4 space-y-2">
                                    <li>Enter a new 4-digit number in the <strong>"Customer Order PIN"</strong> box.</li>
                                    <li>Click <strong>Update</strong> to save the changes.</li>
                                    <li>Update your physical signage (blackboard/menus) so your customers know the new code.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Change this code every morning to prevent old customers from ordering from home.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                {/* Epson Hardware Integration */}
                <section class="bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-8 sm:p-10 border border-stone-200 shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)] relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-5">
                        <Printer size={120} />
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 relative z-10">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-purple-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-purple-100">
                            <Printer size={20} className="text-purple-600" />
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">4. Kitchen Printer Configurations</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prose prose-stone prose-emerald max-w-none relative z-10 space-y-6">
                        <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed">
                            The dashboard features an integrated bypass for Google Chrome's usual Print Dialog box, communicating directly with the **Epson TM-m30III** Thermal POS over your local network. There are two "Routing" modes to accommodate browser security standards:
                        </p>
                        
                        <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden divide-y divide-stone-200">
                            <div class="p-6">
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Mode 1: Direct IP Fetch</h3>
                                <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed mb-4 text-sm">
                                    <strong>How it works:</strong> The dashboard attempts to silently send data directly from your web browser to the printer's local IPv4 Address (e.g. <code class="bg-white font-bold px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-stone-100 text-purple-600 tracking-tighter">http://192.168.1.106</code>).
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed mb-4 text-sm">
                                    <strong>The Catch:</strong> Because your live dashboard is hosted securely on the public internet (using <code>HTTPS://</code>), but your local printer only understands insecure network connections (<code>HTTP://</code>), Google Chrome automatically blocks the connection. This is called the <strong>Mixed Content Rule</strong>.
                                </p>
                                <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-amber-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl">
                                    <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 text-sm mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                                        <AlertCircle size={16} /> Chrome Settings Override (Mandatory)
                                    </h4>
                                    <ol class="text-sm font-medium text-stone-600 list-decimal pl-4 space-y-1">
                                        <li>Open Google Chrome on your Counter PC / Tablet.</li>
                                        <li>Click the <strong>Padlock / Settings Icon</strong> inside the URL bar right next to the site address.</li>
                                        <li>Click on <strong>Site settings</strong>.</li>
                                        <li>Scroll down, look for <strong>Insecure Content</strong>, and change it globally from <em class="text-red-500">Block</em> to <strong class="text-emerald-600 border-b border-emerald-200">Allow</strong>.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="p-6 bg-white">
                                <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3 text-emerald-700">Mode 2: Local Proxy Tool (Recommended)</h3>
                                <p class="text-stone-600 font-medium leading-relaxed mb-4 text-sm">
                                    <strong>How it works:</strong> This mode uses a tiny "invisible helper" script running on your counter computer to bridge the gap between building on the web and printing locally.
                                </p>
                                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                                    <div class="space-y-3">
                                        <h4 class="font-bold text-stone-700 text-sm">1. The Security Hurdle</h4>
                                        <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
                                            Modern browsers block "Mixed Content"—they won't let a secure website (HTTPS) talk to an insecure local device (HTTP). This usually blocks direct printing.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="space-y-3">
                                        <h4 class="font-bold text-stone-700 text-sm">2. The "Localhost" Bypass</h4>
                                        <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
                                            Browsers treat <code class="bg-stone-50 px-1 border border-stone-100 rounded">localhost</code> as a trusted zone. By running a local script, the dashboard can securely "hand over" the print data to your computer, which then delivers it to the printer.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="bg-indigo-50 border-l-4 border-indigo-500 p-4 rounded-r-xl">
                                    <h4 class="font-bold text-indigo-900 text-sm mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                                        <Terminal size={16} /> How to Start the Proxy
                                    </h4>
                                    <p class="text-xs text-indigo-700 mb-3">Execute these commands in your terminal on the counter computer:</p>
                                    <pre class="bg-stone-900 text-stone-300 p-3 rounded-lg text-[11px] font-mono leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto">
cd printer-proxy
npm install
node index.js</pre>
                                    <p class="text-xs text-indigo-700 mt-3 font-medium italic">
                                        Once the terminal says "Proxy Server ACTIVE", toggle the dashboard settings to "Local Proxy".
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </div>
                </section>
            </div>

            {/* Footer Back Link */}
            <div class="mt-12 text-center pb-12">
                <a href="/counter" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-full font-bold text-stone-600 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md hover:bg-stone-50 transition-all active:scale-95 group">
                    <ChevronRight size={18} className="rotate-180 text-stone-400 group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform" />
                    Back to Counter Dashboard
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
